SIMPLE: illinition
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Illinition
<hw>Il`li*ni"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>illinire</ets>, <ets>illinere</ets>, to besmear; pref.
<ets>il-</ets> in, on + <ets>linire</ets>, <ets>linere</ets>, to
smear.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A smearing or rubbing in or on; also,
that which is smeared or rubbed on, as ointment or liniment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A thin crust of some extraneous substance formed on
minerals.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A thin crust or <qex>illinition</qex> of black manganese.</q>
<rj><qau>Kirwan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Illinois</ent>⟦br⟧
